526
00:40:38,708 --> 00:40:39,537
There we go.

527
00:40:40,777 --> 00:40:43,108
For one brief moment I saw all the bolts silhouetted...

528
00:40:43,179 --> 00:40:45,703
against the lights of the traffic. And then they were gone.

529
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:52,578
Oh, fudge!

530
00:40:53,289 --> 00:40:55,188
Only I didn't say "fudge."

531
00:40:55,291 --> 00:40:57,121
I said the word.

532
00:40:57,326 --> 00:41:00,556
The big one. The queen mother of dirty words.

533
00:41:00,897 --> 00:41:03,296
The "f, dash, dash, dash" word.

534
00:41:03,366 --> 00:41:05,265
What did you say?

535
00:41:08,203 --> 00:41:10,898
That's what I thought you said.

536
00:41:13,376 --> 00:41:15,172
Get in the car.

537
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:19,103
Go on.

538
00:41:19,182 --> 00:41:21,445
It was all over. I was dead.

539
00:41:21,684 --> 00:41:24,311
What would it be? The guillotine? Hanging?

540
00:41:24,387 --> 00:41:27,287
The chair? The rack? The Chinese water torture?

541
00:41:27,790 --> 00:41:31,782
Mere child's play compared to what surely awaited me.

542
00:41:34,630 --> 00:41:36,893
Everything go all right?

543
00:41:51,613 --> 00:41:53,307
Eight minutes.

544
00:41:55,617 --> 00:41:57,949
Do you know what your son just said?

545
00:41:57,951 --> 00:41:58,950
No. What?

546
00:41:59,689 --> 00:42:01,986
I'll tell you what he said. Randy!

547
00:42:05,661 --> 00:42:06,388
Ralphie!

548
00:42:08,497 --> 00:42:11,397
Over the years, I got to be quite a connoisseur of soap.

549
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:15,697
My personal preference is for Lux, but I found Palmolive had a nice...

550
00:42:15,871 --> 00:42:17,963
piquant, after-dinner flavor.

551
00:42:18,039 --> 00:42:21,565
Heady, but with just a touch of mellow smoothness.

552
00:42:24,980 --> 00:42:27,379
Lifebuoy, on the other hand...

553
00:42:29,384 --> 00:42:31,248
You ready to tell me?

554
00:42:35,957 --> 00:42:38,516
All right. Where did you hear that word?

555
00:42:38,694 --> 00:42:42,595
Now I had heard that word at least 10 times a day from my old man.

556
00:42:42,764 --> 00:42:45,061
My father worked in profanity the way...

557
00:42:45,166 --> 00:42:47,599
other artists might work in oils or clay.

558
00:42:47,702 --> 00:42:50,397
It was his true medium. A master.

559
00:42:50,472 --> 00:42:52,871
But I chickened out. And I blurted out...

560
00:42:53,041 --> 00:42:55,008
the first name that came to mind.

561
00:42:55,076 --> 00:42:56,337
Schwartz!

562
00:42:58,046 --> 00:42:59,637
I see.

563
00:43:11,025 --> 00:43:13,891
Hello, Mrs. Schwartz? Yes, I'm fine.

564
00:43:14,428 --> 00:43:17,885
Mrs. Schwartz, do you know what Ralph just said?

565
00:43:19,700 --> 00:43:20,666
No.

566
00:43:20,936 --> 00:43:22,459
He said...

567
00:43:24,439 --> 00:43:25,962
Not that!

568
00:43:26,174 --> 00:43:27,435
Yes, that.

569
00:43:27,576 --> 00:43:29,044
Do you know where he heard it?

570
00:43:29,045 --> 00:43:30,644
Probably from his father.

571
00:43:30,645 --> 00:43:33,135
No! He heard it from your son!

572
00:43:33,214 --> 00:43:34,202
What?

573
00:43:42,290 --> 00:43:43,551
What'd I do, Mom?

574
00:43:44,325 --> 00:43:46,292
Why? I didn't do nothing!

575
00:43:51,332 --> 00:43:54,994
Another shot of mysterious, inexorable, official justice.

576
00:43:55,569 --> 00:44:00,335
Rinse out and go to bed. Am I glad you finished your homework!

577
00:44:00,507 --> 00:44:03,441
Get right into bed, and I don't want to see any lights on.

578
00:44:03,511 --> 00:44:06,479
You are being punished, so no comic book reading!

579
00:44:06,581 --> 00:44:08,571
I'll come in, and if any lights are on...

580
00:44:08,683 --> 00:44:11,583
Don't you give me that look! You're gonna get it!

581
00:44:33,340 --> 00:44:36,103
Three blocks away, Schwartz was getting his.

582
00:44:37,745 --> 00:44:40,144
There has never been a kid who didn't believe...

583
00:44:40,347 --> 00:44:44,214
vaguely but insistently, that he would be stricken blind...

584
00:44:44,385 --> 00:44:48,184
before he reached 21. And then they'd be sorry.

585
00:44:58,966 --> 00:45:00,762
Why, it's Ralph!

586
00:45:01,635 --> 00:45:04,865
Well, come on in, Ralph. Where've you been?

587
00:45:09,877 --> 00:45:11,207
Why, he's carrying a cane!

588
00:45:11,278 --> 00:45:12,767
What is it, Ralph? What happened?

589
00:45:12,846 --> 00:45:14,710
Why, he's blind!

590
00:45:14,782 --> 00:45:16,612
Blind? Oh, my God!

591
00:45:19,752 --> 00:45:21,412
Ralph, is it something we did?

592
00:45:21,521 --> 00:45:24,353
What brought you to this lonely state?

593
00:45:25,658 --> 00:45:28,592
Ralph, please tell us no matter how it hurts. What did we do?

594
00:45:29,463 --> 00:45:31,225
Look, I can't.

595
00:45:31,298 --> 00:45:33,197
Please, Ralph. I must know what we did.

596
00:45:33,434 --> 00:45:35,333
What brought you to this?

597
00:45:44,845 --> 00:45:47,005
Soap poisoning.

598
00:45:54,020 --> 00:45:56,214
Oh, how could we do it?

599
00:45:56,889 --> 00:45:59,948
I'll manage to get along, somehow.

600
00:46:00,927 --> 00:46:02,360
I'll never forgive myself.

601
00:46:02,361 --> 00:46:03,360
Thanks, Mom.

602
00:46:03,529 --> 00:46:06,122
I told you not to use Lifebuoy.

603
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:08,996
I feel awful!

604
00:46:34,026 --> 00:46:34,889
Thank you, Heather.

605
00:46:34,961 --> 00:46:35,857
Merry Christmas.

606
00:46:35,858 --> 00:46:36,757
Merry Christmas.

607
00:46:37,563 --> 00:46:38,358
Thank you, Flick.

608
00:46:39,031 --> 00:46:40,554
Merry Christmas, Miss Shields.

609
00:47:05,625 --> 00:47:08,650
I just thought that you'd be getting tired of the same old stuff.

610
00:47:08,761 --> 00:47:12,025
Yes, truly, a little bribe never hurts.

611
00:47:12,565 --> 00:47:14,623
Well, thank you very much, Ralph.

612
00:47:20,072 --> 00:47:21,868
Merry Christmas.

613
00:47:24,609 --> 00:47:25,870
Happy New Year.

614
00:47:28,713 --> 00:47:30,771
You can take your seat now, Ralph.

615
00:47:54,373 --> 00:47:57,432
The weeks of drinking gallons of Ovaltine, in order to get...

616
00:47:57,542 --> 00:48:00,977
the Ovaltine inner seal to send off for my Little Orphan Annie...

617
00:48:01,046 --> 00:48:04,572
secret decoder pen, was about to pay off.

618
00:48:05,350 --> 00:48:08,045
I got it. "Master Ralph Parker."

619
00:48:08,119 --> 00:48:09,847
My decoder pen!

620
00:48:14,226 --> 00:48:15,692
All right!

621
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:23,832
"Be it known to all that Ralph Parker is hereby appointed...

622
00:48:23,903 --> 00:48:26,666
"a member of the Little Orphan Annie secret circle and...

623
00:48:26,739 --> 00:48:29,639
"is entitled to all the honors and benefits occurring thereto."

624
00:48:30,175 --> 00:48:32,301
Signed, Little Orphan Annie.

625
00:48:32,544 --> 00:48:34,909
Countersigned, Pierre Andre!

626
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:36,576
In ink!

627
00:48:36,748 --> 00:48:40,308
Honors and benefits. Already at the age of nine.

628
00:48:46,157 --> 00:48:47,487
Come on. Let's get on with it.

629
00:48:47,559 --> 00:48:50,527
I don't need all that jazz about smugglers and pirates.

630
00:48:51,563 --> 00:48:54,122
Listen tomorrow night for the concluding adventure of...

631
00:48:54,232 --> 00:48:57,223
The Black Pirate Ship. Now it's time...

632
00:48:57,369 --> 00:49:01,429
for Annie's secret message for you members of the secret circle.

633
00:49:02,207 --> 00:49:04,299
Remember, kids, only members of...

634
00:49:04,376 --> 00:49:08,436
Annie's secret circle can decode Annie's secret message.

635
00:49:08,647 --> 00:49:11,740
Remember, Annie is depending on you.

636
00:49:12,684 --> 00:49:14,844
Set your pins to B-2.

637
00:49:15,220 --> 00:49:17,346
Here is the message.

638
00:49:17,622 --> 00:49:18,986
12. 11. 2...

639
00:49:19,057 --> 00:49:21,524
I am in my first secret meeting.

640
00:49:21,593 --> 00:49:24,356
...25. 14. 11. 18.

641
00:49:25,430 --> 00:49:26,191
16. 23...

642
00:49:26,264 --> 00:49:27,958
Pierre was in great voice tonight.

643
00:49:28,033 --> 00:49:31,798
I could tell that tonight's message was really important.

644
00:49:32,202 --> 00:49:33,259
...3. 25.

645
00:49:33,370 --> 00:49:37,533
That's a message from Annie herself. Remember, don't tell anyone.

646
00:49:41,345 --> 00:49:44,313
Ninety seconds later I'm in the only room in the house...

647
00:49:44,382 --> 00:49:47,680
where a boy of nine can sit in privacy and decode.

648
00:49:50,188 --> 00:49:52,747
Ah! "B." I went to the next.

649
00:49:53,758 --> 00:49:56,385
"E." The first word is "be"!

650
00:49:56,861 --> 00:49:59,954
"S." It was coming easier now. "U."

651
00:50:01,766 --> 00:50:04,359
Come on, Ralphie! I gotta go.

652
00:50:05,035 --> 00:50:06,763
I'll be right down, Ma.

653
00:50:06,870 --> 00:50:08,268
Gee whiz.

654
00:50:10,774 --> 00:50:12,866
"T. O."

655
00:50:13,911 --> 00:50:16,310
"Be sure to." Be sure to what?

656
00:50:16,413 --> 00:50:19,142
What was Little Orphan Annie trying to say? Be sure to what?

657
00:50:19,350 --> 00:50:22,341
Ralphie! Randy has got to go! Will you please come out?

658
00:50:22,419 --> 00:50:25,148
All right, Ma! I'll be right out!

659
00:50:25,523 --> 00:50:26,989
I was getting closer now.

660
00:50:27,092 --> 00:50:30,060
The tension was terrible. What was it?

661
00:50:30,128 --> 00:50:32,357
The fate of the planet may hang in the balance.

662
00:50:32,897 --> 00:50:34,955
Ralphie! Randy's gotta go!

663
00:50:35,899 --> 00:50:38,526
I'll be right out, for crying out loud!

664
00:50:38,902 --> 00:50:41,631
Almost there! My fingers flew.

665
00:50:41,739 --> 00:50:43,399
My mind was a steel trap.

666
00:50:43,507 --> 00:50:44,905
Every pore vibrated.

667
00:50:45,309 --> 00:50:46,969
It was almost clear.

668
00:50:47,144 --> 00:50:48,167
Yes!

669
00:50:55,352 --> 00:50:56,579
Ovaltine?

670
00:51:00,324 --> 00:51:02,052
A crummy commercial?

671
00:51:04,695 --> 00:51:06,218
Son of a bitch!

672
00:51:08,465 --> 00:51:10,955
I went out to face the world again.

673
00:51:11,101 --> 00:51:12,533
Wiser.

674
00:51:25,482 --> 00:51:26,948
Red cabbage?

675
00:51:27,017 --> 00:51:29,985
No, that's for tomorrow night. You love red cabbage, Ralphie.

676
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:33,889
You filthy system!

677
00:51:33,957 --> 00:51:35,617
I hate it!

678
00:51:35,793 --> 00:51:38,420
Schmucker! Smelly watt-buster!

679
00:51:47,136 --> 00:51:51,504
What happened next was a family controversy for years.

680
00:52:08,425 --> 00:52:09,550
What was that? What happened?

681
00:52:13,796 --> 00:52:15,228
What happened?

682
00:52:15,998 --> 00:52:17,487
What broke?

683
00:52:17,767 --> 00:52:19,529
I don't know what happened.

684
00:52:19,602 --> 00:52:21,865
I was watering my plant and...

685
00:52:23,172 --> 00:52:24,934
I broke your lamp.

686
00:52:40,124 --> 00:52:41,784
Don't you touch that!

687
00:52:42,792 --> 00:52:44,918
You were always jealous of this lamp.

688
00:52:45,661 --> 00:52:47,127
Jealous of a plastic leg?

689
00:52:47,230 --> 00:52:48,389
Jealous!

690
00:52:48,564 --> 00:52:50,793
Jealous because I won.

691
00:52:52,702 --> 00:52:54,191
That's ridiculous! Jealous?

692
00:52:54,337 --> 00:52:55,462
Jealous of what?

693
00:52:56,706 --> 00:52:58,002
That is...

694
00:52:58,074 --> 00:53:02,032
the ugliest lamp I have ever seen in my entire life!

695
00:53:02,411 --> 00:53:03,968
Now it was out.

696
00:53:04,380 --> 00:53:05,676
Get the glue.

697
00:53:06,249 --> 00:53:08,512
We're out of glue.

698
00:53:10,820 --> 00:53:15,153
You used up all the glue on purpose!

699
00:53:16,993 --> 00:53:19,392
The old man stood quivering with fury...

700
00:53:19,495 --> 00:53:21,928
stammering as he tried to come up with a real crusher.

701
00:53:22,331 --> 00:53:23,592
All he got out was:

702
00:53:23,666 --> 00:53:24,962
Not a finger!

703
00:54:05,708 --> 00:54:07,937
With as much dignity as he could muster...

704
00:54:08,044 --> 00:54:10,603
the old man gathered up the sad remains...

705
00:54:10,713 --> 00:54:13,237
of his shattered major award.

706
00:54:14,116 --> 00:54:16,913
Later that night, alone in the backyard...

707
00:54:17,319 --> 00:54:19,149
he buried it next to the garage.

708
00:54:19,754 --> 00:54:21,414
Now I could never be sure...

709
00:54:21,890 --> 00:54:25,484
but I thought that I heard the sound of taps being played...

710
00:54:25,794 --> 00:54:27,055
gently.

711
00:54:27,462 --> 00:54:29,190
Know what I'm getting my old man for Christmas?

712
00:54:29,264 --> 00:54:30,060
What?

713
00:54:30,061 --> 00:54:31,060
A rose that squirts.

714
00:54:31,132 --> 00:54:33,190
People come to smell it, it squirts them.

715
00:54:33,368 --> 00:54:35,494
I'm getting my old man a Flit gun.

716
00:54:35,495 --> 00:54:36,894
A Flit gun?

717
00:54:40,243 --> 00:54:41,402
Stop right there!

718
00:54:41,611 --> 00:54:45,546
Ordinarily, if Dill so much as said "hi" to you, you felt great...

719
00:54:46,048 --> 00:54:49,574
warm inside. But mostly he just hit you in the mouth.

720
00:54:49,851 --> 00:54:52,512
I can't now, Grover. I've gotta go see Miss Shields.

721
00:54:52,854 --> 00:54:55,754
Hey, come here! Get over here!

722
00:54:56,191 --> 00:54:58,124
Come on, you! Hey, come here!

723
00:54:59,628 --> 00:55:00,559
You! Come here!

724
00:55:00,795 --> 00:55:01,522
Who, me?

725
00:55:01,763 --> 00:55:03,163
No, your Aunt Tilly.

726
00:55:03,164 --> 00:55:04,663
Yeah, you. Get over here!

727
00:55:04,866 --> 00:55:07,857
I left Flick to certain annihilation.

728
00:55:08,903 --> 00:55:11,393
But BB gun mania knows no loyalties.

729
00:55:11,873 --> 00:55:13,840
Uncle! Uncle!

730
00:55:18,813 --> 00:55:19,836
All right, class.

731
00:55:20,281 --> 00:55:22,874
I have your Christmas themes for you.

732
00:55:23,918 --> 00:55:25,282
I'm pleased.

733
00:55:25,887 --> 00:55:28,081
In general, you did very well.

734
00:55:31,259 --> 00:55:34,785
However, I was disappointed in the margins.

735
00:55:37,432 --> 00:55:39,023
This is it.

736
00:55:40,402 --> 00:55:42,596
"C+"? No, it can't be.

737
00:55:43,038 --> 00:55:44,436
C+?

738
00:55:44,606 --> 00:55:46,630
C+!

739
00:55:54,415 --> 00:55:55,642
Oh, no!

740
00:55:56,817 --> 00:55:58,477
"You'll shoot your eye out"?

741
00:56:00,821 --> 00:56:02,788
My mother must have gotten to Miss Shields.

742
00:56:02,956 --> 00:56:04,547
There could be no other explanation.

743
00:56:04,826 --> 00:56:08,955
You'll shoot your eye out. You'll shoot your eye out.

744
00:56:11,533 --> 00:56:15,263
Was there no end to this conspiracy of irrational prejudice...

745
00:56:15,337 --> 00:56:17,634
against Red Ryder and his peacemaker?

746
00:56:17,839 --> 00:56:22,036
These multiplication questions were most missed in our last math test.

747
00:56:22,143 --> 00:56:23,700
Would you answer in unison, please?

748
00:56:24,011 --> 00:56:26,911
I was surrounded by happier kids who were all going to get...

749
00:56:27,014 --> 00:56:28,571
what they wanted for Christmas.

750
00:56:28,949 --> 00:56:30,176
...fifty-six.

751
00:57:00,848 --> 00:57:02,371
Hey, four-eyes!

752
00:57:02,449 --> 00:57:05,008
How'd you like your snowball sandwich?

753
00:57:05,686 --> 00:57:07,676
Maybe you'd like another one!

754
00:57:13,227 --> 00:57:14,215
Listen, jerk.

755
00:57:14,461 --> 00:57:17,759
When I tell you to come, you better come!

756
00:57:18,966 --> 00:57:21,433
What? Are you going to cry now?

757
00:57:21,635 --> 00:57:25,400
Come on, cry baby, cry for me. Come on.

758
00:57:25,773 --> 00:57:27,262
Cry!

759
00:57:27,407 --> 00:57:29,203
Deep in the recesses of my brain...

760
00:57:29,343 --> 00:57:32,709
a tiny red-hot little flame began to grow.

761
00:57:46,460 --> 00:57:47,585
Something had happened.

762
00:57:47,761 --> 00:57:51,753
A fuse blew and I had gone out of my skull.

763
00:58:00,873 --> 00:58:03,306
I'm telling my dad!

764
00:58:04,710 --> 00:58:06,802
Hey, Ralphie!

765
00:58:13,654 --> 00:58:15,780
Beat him up! Beat him up!

766
00:58:30,269 --> 00:58:32,532
Did you hear what he said?

767
00:58:37,143 --> 00:58:39,576
I have since heard of people under...

768
00:58:39,679 --> 00:58:43,341
extreme duress speaking in strange tongues.

769
00:58:43,649 --> 00:58:47,106
I became conscious that a steady torrent of obscenities...

770
00:58:47,286 --> 00:58:51,585
and swearing of all kinds was pouring out of me as I screamed.

771
00:59:00,434 --> 00:59:01,991
Ralphie!

772
00:59:18,885 --> 00:59:20,749
We're going home. Come on.

773
00:59:39,872 --> 00:59:42,840
Calm down. Come on in here, Ralph.

774
00:59:47,346 --> 00:59:48,778
Put your head down in here.

775
00:59:49,215 --> 00:59:51,375
Come on, get down in here.

776
00:59:52,485 --> 00:59:54,042
Settle down.

777
00:59:56,355 --> 01:00:00,085
I want you to go in there and lie down in your room for a while.

778
01:00:01,193 --> 01:00:03,319
Ralphie, just settle down.

779
01:00:07,032 --> 01:00:08,794
Here, dry off.

780
01:00:09,034 --> 01:00:11,001
All right, calm down.

781
01:00:11,136 --> 01:00:13,569
All right. Now go lie down.

782
01:00:33,326 --> 01:00:35,885
The light was getting purple and soft outside.

783
01:00:36,028 --> 01:00:38,860
Almost time for my father to come home from work.

784
01:00:59,250 --> 01:01:00,841
What's the matter? What you crying for?

785
01:01:01,821 --> 01:01:04,254
Daddy's going to kill Ralphie.

786
01:01:04,857 --> 01:01:06,323
No, he's not.

787
01:01:06,459 --> 01:01:07,823
Yes, he is, too.

788
01:01:07,927 --> 01:01:09,484
No, he's not.

789
01:01:09,594 --> 01:01:13,791
I promise you Daddy is not going to kill Ralphie.

790
01:01:14,666 --> 01:01:16,189
Why don't you come on out of there?

791
01:01:19,771 --> 01:01:20,930
Would you like some milk?

792
01:01:22,807 --> 01:01:24,535
You would?

793
01:01:31,182 --> 01:01:32,375
Here you go.

794
01:01:33,718 --> 01:01:34,741
All right?

795
01:01:35,453 --> 01:01:38,182
I'll see you later? Okay. Bye.

796
01:01:50,502 --> 01:01:54,164
I heard the car roar up the driveway, and a wave of terror broke over me.

797
01:01:54,406 --> 01:01:57,431
He'll know what I said, the awful things that I said.

798
01:01:57,676 --> 01:01:59,472
Get out of here!

799
01:02:00,145 --> 01:02:03,409
Go on home, you mangy mutts. Get out of here, you rotten, filthy...

800
01:02:03,682 --> 01:02:04,409
Hey, Bumpus!

801
01:02:04,482 --> 01:02:06,949
Get over here and get your stinking dogs!

802
01:02:08,053 --> 01:02:11,112
Hey, come on, what's for dinner? I'm starving to death.

803
01:02:31,009 --> 01:02:33,636
Well, what happened today?

804
01:02:34,345 --> 01:02:35,675
Where's your glasses?

805
01:02:37,115 --> 01:02:38,775
Did you lose your glasses again?

806
01:02:39,150 --> 01:02:40,081
Ralphie.

807
01:02:40,418 --> 01:02:43,511
Remember, you left these on the radio again.

808
01:02:43,754 --> 01:02:46,586
Now try not to do that anymore.

809
01:02:47,624 --> 01:02:49,181
So what else happened today?

810
01:02:50,694 --> 01:02:52,092
Nothing much.

811
01:02:52,296 --> 01:02:53,626
Ralphie had a fight.

812
01:02:54,431 --> 01:02:55,192
A fight?

813
01:02:55,399 --> 01:02:56,729
What kind of a fight?

814
01:02:59,169 --> 01:03:01,227
You know how boys are.

815
01:03:02,873 --> 01:03:04,772
I gave him a talking to.

816
01:03:06,176 --> 01:03:09,542
I see that the Bears are playing Green Bay on Sunday.

817
01:03:11,416 --> 01:03:12,177
Oh, yeah.

818
01:03:12,350 --> 01:03:14,374
Zudock's got tickets. I wish I had.

819
01:03:14,686 --> 01:03:16,585
He'll freeze his keister off out there.

820
01:03:19,656 --> 01:03:23,147
I slowly began to realize I was not about to be destroyed.

821
01:03:23,527 --> 01:03:24,993
The Chicago Bears.

822
01:03:25,596 --> 01:03:27,085
The terror of the midway.

823
01:03:28,065 --> 01:03:31,556
From then on, things were different between me and my mother.

824
01:03:33,837 --> 01:03:36,896
More like the Chicago Chipmunks, maybe.

825
01:03:37,074 --> 01:03:38,199
But Bears, never.

826
01:03:40,177 --> 01:03:41,165
Strange.

827
01:03:41,445 --> 01:03:45,175
Even something as monumental as "The Scut Farkus Affair"...

828
01:03:45,415 --> 01:03:46,938
as it came to be known...

829
01:03:47,116 --> 01:03:49,709
was pushed out of my mind as I struggled for a way out...

830
01:03:49,786 --> 01:03:52,618
of the impenetrable BB gun web...

831
01:03:52,689 --> 01:03:54,747
in which my mother had me trapped.

832
01:03:55,092 --> 01:03:56,183
Santa!

833
01:03:56,894 --> 01:03:58,622
Yeah, I'll ask Santa.

834
01:03:59,329 --> 01:04:00,989
Of course! Santa.

835
01:04:01,298 --> 01:04:03,356
The big man. The head honcho.

836
01:04:03,600 --> 01:04:04,827
The connection.

837
01:04:05,102 --> 01:04:07,695
My mother had slipped up this time.

838
01:04:29,859 --> 01:04:31,485
Mickey!

839
01:04:48,545 --> 01:04:51,104
The store's going to close soon
and Santa will be gone.

840
01:04:51,180 --> 01:04:55,206
Ralphie, Santa's not going anyplace. Just be still!

841
01:05:04,861 --> 01:05:07,294
Mom, this is just the same old dumb parade as last year.

842
01:05:07,396 --> 01:05:09,692
Ralphie, will you please calm down.

843
01:05:09,693 --> 01:05:10,592
Mom--

844
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:11,626
Hush!

845
01:05:11,627 --> 01:05:12,626
Shut up, Ralphie!

846
01:05:22,245 --> 01:05:23,040
There he is!

847
01:05:23,112 --> 01:05:25,272
Santa!

848
01:05:32,588 --> 01:05:35,078
Have you been a good boy? Have you?

849
01:05:35,224 --> 01:05:36,956
Can we go now? Can we go?

850
01:05:36,957 --> 01:05:38,056
Yes, we can go now.

851
01:05:38,194 --> 01:05:40,388
Come on, Ralphie.

852
01:05:52,041 --> 01:05:54,133
Merry Christmas!

853
01:05:56,845 --> 01:05:59,210
Come on, Randy, hurry up.

854
01:06:12,328 --> 01:06:14,522
Ralphie, look over there.

855
01:06:14,597 --> 01:06:17,622
See, the line's not so long. Get in it.

856
01:06:17,700 --> 01:06:20,566
Take Randy's hand and hold on to him. We'll see you later, okay?

857
01:06:20,636 --> 01:06:23,798
Stay together, you hear? And don't get lost.

858
01:06:27,375 --> 01:06:28,466
Come on.

859
01:06:28,610 --> 01:06:30,076
Let's go.

860
01:06:32,981 --> 01:06:34,607
Young man.

861
01:06:34,783 --> 01:06:35,908
Hey, kid.

862
01:06:36,284 --> 01:06:38,044
Just where do you think you're going?

863
01:06:38,045 --> 01:06:39,844
We're going up to see Santa.

864
01:06:40,689 --> 01:06:43,486
The line ends here. It begins there.

865
01:06:43,926 --> 01:06:45,620
Merry Christmas!

866
01:06:45,828 --> 01:06:48,921
Come on, come up, boys and girls.
Hurry up.

867
01:06:54,837 --> 01:06:56,269
Come on.

868
01:07:00,175 --> 01:07:04,975
The line waiting to see Santa stretched all the way back to Terre Haute!

869
01:07:05,613 --> 01:07:07,512
And I was at the end of it.

870
01:07:09,851 --> 01:07:11,909
I like Santa.

871
01:07:16,291 --> 01:07:18,485
Let's face it. Most of us were scoffers.

872
01:07:18,560 --> 01:07:23,587
Moments before zero hour, it did not pay to take chances.

873
01:07:24,533 --> 01:07:28,662
The chocolate snowman eats little boys.

874
01:07:30,405 --> 01:07:31,962
My pretty...

875
01:07:32,207 --> 01:07:34,333
What a tasty little boy.

876
01:07:35,610 --> 01:07:38,510
Don't bother me. I'm thinking.

877
01:07:42,917 --> 01:07:45,043
I like The Wizard of Oz.

878
01:07:48,323 --> 01:07:50,256
I like the Tin Man.

879
01:07:54,462 --> 01:07:58,557
If Higbee thinks I'm working one minute past 9:00, he can kiss my foot.

880
01:08:00,201 --> 01:08:02,259
Come on up on Santa's lap.

881
01:08:02,369 --> 01:08:06,805
There's a wet one. And what's your name, little boy?

882
01:08:07,008 --> 01:08:07,996
Billy.

883
01:08:08,076 --> 01:08:09,269
Come on, Randy.

884
01:08:10,845 --> 01:08:14,041
And what do you want for Christmas, Billy? A toy truck?

885
01:08:14,149 --> 01:08:16,082
Get him off my lap.

886
01:08:16,217 --> 01:08:18,013
Quick, get me a towel.

887
01:08:25,760 --> 01:08:27,852
I hate the smell of tapioca.

888
01:08:29,397 --> 01:08:32,832
Attention shoppers! It is now 9:00 and our store is closing.

889
01:08:33,233 --> 01:08:36,167
9:00! Great Scott! The store is gonna close!

890
01:08:37,204 --> 01:08:39,797
Santa can't wait all night.

891
01:08:40,374 --> 01:08:42,466
Come on up on Santa's lap.

892
01:08:52,253 --> 01:08:53,378
Get moving, kid.

893
01:08:54,722 --> 01:08:56,416
Quit dragging your feet.

894
01:09:09,536 --> 01:09:11,093
Get him out of here.

895
01:09:21,815 --> 01:09:23,577
Come on, kid.

896
01:09:29,656 --> 01:09:32,146
Come on up.

897
01:09:42,503 --> 01:09:45,994
And what's your name, little boy?

898
01:09:46,140 --> 01:09:49,575
Hey, kid, hurry up, the store's closing!

899
01:09:52,613 --> 01:09:57,276
Listen, little boy, we got a lot of people waiting here, so get going!

900
01:09:59,486 --> 01:10:02,454
What do you want for Christmas, little boy?

901
01:10:02,823 --> 01:10:04,915
My mind had gone blank.

902
01:10:05,058 --> 01:10:07,287
Frantically I tried to remember what it was I wanted.

903
01:10:07,360 --> 01:10:08,917
I was blowing it, blowing it.

904
01:10:11,964 --> 01:10:15,023
How about a nice football?

905
01:10:15,169 --> 01:10:18,160
Football. What's a football?

906
01:10:18,872 --> 01:10:20,998
Without conscious will, my voice squeaked out:

907
01:10:21,108 --> 01:10:22,335
Football.

908
01:10:22,876 --> 01:10:24,467
Okay, get him out of here.

909
01:10:25,012 --> 01:10:28,344
A football! Oh, no. What was I doing?

910
01:10:28,415 --> 01:10:30,780
Wake up, stupid, wake up!

911
01:10:38,592 --> 01:10:41,685
I want an official Red Ryder carbine-action 200-shot...

912
01:10:41,794 --> 01:10:42,851
range model air rifle.

913
01:10:44,931 --> 01:10:46,625
You'll shoot your eye out, kid.

914
01:10:48,367 --> 01:10:50,163
Merry Christmas.

915
01:11:05,886 --> 01:11:07,682
I'll see you in Oz, folks.

916
01:11:16,262 --> 01:11:18,229
Well, did you see Santa Claus?

917
01:11:18,798 --> 01:11:21,231
Did you tell him what you wanted for Christmas?

918
01:11:21,334 --> 01:11:25,064
Did he ask you if you'd been a good boy all year?

919
01:11:25,471 --> 01:11:26,198
No.

920
01:11:27,039 --> 01:11:29,165
Don't worry, he knows.

921
01:11:29,875 --> 01:11:31,398
He always knows.

922
01:11:34,180 --> 01:11:36,807
Merry Christmas.

923
01:11:37,750 --> 01:11:40,081
Okay, down you go.

924
01:11:40,354 --> 01:11:41,513
Bye, Chris.

925
01:11:51,864 --> 01:11:54,161
That's fine.

926
01:11:54,967 --> 01:11:57,526
Now wait a minute. All right. Plug her in!

927
01:11:59,438 --> 01:12:01,064
Well, the green string is out.

928
01:12:01,173 --> 01:12:03,436
No, the green is on. It's the blue that's out.

929
01:12:03,709 --> 01:12:05,801
Oh, don't tell me what color it is.

930
01:12:05,911 --> 01:12:07,070
I'm not color blind.

931
01:12:07,847 --> 01:12:09,336
I'm not color blind, either.

932
01:12:13,019 --> 01:12:14,508
There, see, I told you it was green.

933
01:12:17,022 --> 01:12:19,148
Hold it! Don't anybody move!

934
01:12:20,626 --> 01:12:22,024
Hold it right there!

935
01:12:22,662 --> 01:12:24,424
A fuse is out.

936
01:12:24,930 --> 01:12:28,626
The old man could replace fuses quicker than a jackrabbit on a date.

937
01:12:28,701 --> 01:12:30,327
He bought them by the gross.

938
01:12:36,242 --> 01:12:37,970
Oh, Ralph.

939
01:12:38,277 --> 01:12:40,642
My, isn't that pretty?

940
01:12:40,813 --> 01:12:42,109
That son of a gun.

941
01:12:44,083 --> 01:12:45,276
Yeah. No.

942
01:12:45,418 --> 01:12:47,078
That star is crooked.

943
01:12:47,352 --> 01:12:49,285
That star is perfectly straight.

944
01:12:51,790 --> 01:12:53,282
Oh, you've got to be careful.

945
01:12:53,283 --> 01:12:53,882
I am.

946
01:12:56,594 --> 01:12:59,721
It's just... Let me get it fixed. That's all right.

947
01:13:05,805 --> 01:13:07,328
Perfect.

948
01:13:10,209 --> 01:13:12,039
Oh, goodness, look at the time.

949
01:13:12,111 --> 01:13:14,101
I hope Santa hasn't had to pass up this house...

950
01:13:14,180 --> 01:13:17,205
just because some boys weren't in bed when he came by.

951
01:13:17,350 --> 01:13:19,943
I thought I heard Santa's sleigh bells...

952
01:13:20,018 --> 01:13:22,542
a little while ago, going up the other side of the street.

953
01:13:23,621 --> 01:13:24,951
All right, you two, upstairs.

954
01:13:26,091 --> 01:13:28,115
Go on the double, on the double.

955
01:13:39,637 --> 01:13:40,728
Okay, let's get them.

956
01:14:44,102 --> 01:14:46,160
Randy, come on! Get up, Randy!

957
01:14:56,880 --> 01:14:58,972
Santa Claus had come!

958
01:15:02,553 --> 01:15:04,747
Wow! A truck! That's mine!

959
01:15:05,322 --> 01:15:07,551
Wow, look over here! That's mine!

960
01:15:07,624 --> 01:15:09,113
What's in here?

961
01:15:09,460 --> 01:15:10,483
It's hard.

962
01:15:10,829 --> 01:15:13,888
Fire truck. Oh boy, that's mine!

963
01:15:22,974 --> 01:15:24,270
Does this raise?

964
01:15:39,456 --> 01:15:40,683
Merry Christmas.

965
01:15:42,159 --> 01:15:44,490
Merry Christmas, you two.

966
01:15:45,295 --> 01:15:47,990
Randy, no. Wait for Christmas to start, honey.

967
01:15:48,432 --> 01:15:49,891
I want to play Santa!

968
01:15:49,892 --> 01:15:51,491
Well, wait a minute, Randy.

969
01:15:51,568 --> 01:15:53,467
He played Santa last year, didn't he?

970
01:15:53,838 --> 01:15:55,964
Ralphie, you play Santa this time.

971
01:15:56,240 --> 01:15:57,073
Come on, Ralphie.

972
01:15:57,074 --> 01:15:58,173
Who should I start with?

973
01:15:58,475 --> 01:16:00,772
Well, give Randy a present.

974
01:16:00,878 --> 01:16:05,041
And, I think I see Aunt Clara's gift to you right over there.

975
01:16:05,148 --> 01:16:07,581
She always sends you such wonderful presents.

976
01:16:07,951 --> 01:16:10,646
Give me mine, Ralphie! Come on.

977
01:16:27,538 --> 01:16:32,031
Christmas had come. Officially. We plunged into the cornucopia...

978
01:16:32,108 --> 01:16:35,975
quivering with desire and the ecstasy of unbridled avarice.

979
01:16:36,113 --> 01:16:37,545
Didn't I get a tie this year?

980
01:16:44,688 --> 01:16:46,286
A zeppelin!

981
01:16:46,287 --> 01:16:47,986
A can of Simonize.

982
01:16:48,792 --> 01:16:51,954
Ralphie, what did Aunt Clara give you? Show everybody.

983
01:16:57,134 --> 01:16:57,997
I don't want to.

984
01:16:58,602 --> 01:17:01,035
Ralphie, show everybody what Aunt Clara gave you.

985
01:17:01,971 --> 01:17:04,803
Aunt Clara had for years labored under the delusion that...

986
01:17:04,874 --> 01:17:09,401
I was not only perpetually four years old, but also a girl.

987
01:17:09,912 --> 01:17:13,779
She just always gives you the nicest things, Ralphie.

988
01:17:18,288 --> 01:17:21,085
Oh, isn't that sweet?

989
01:17:21,525 --> 01:17:23,222
Ralph, go upstairs and try it on you--

990
01:17:23,223 --> 01:17:24,322
I don't want to!

991
01:17:24,428 --> 01:17:26,827
Go upstairs right now and try on that present!

992
01:17:26,930 --> 01:17:30,296
She went to all that trouble to make it! Now go on.

993
01:17:37,974 --> 01:17:42,137
While Ralphie is changing, I'm going to play Santa Claus.

994
01:17:42,211 --> 01:17:43,837
Now, let me see what can I find.

995
01:17:44,046 --> 01:17:47,606
I see something! Randy.

996
01:17:47,850 --> 01:17:49,612
This is for you, honey.

997
01:17:50,486 --> 01:17:52,419
And this is for Daddy.

998
01:17:55,358 --> 01:17:56,051
Here.

999
01:17:56,125 --> 01:17:57,989
From me to you.

1000
01:18:00,263 --> 01:18:02,093
Thanks a lot.

1001
01:18:02,499 --> 01:18:04,728
I wonder what it could be?

1002
01:18:05,735 --> 01:18:08,726
Only one way to find out, isn't there?

1003
01:18:09,005 --> 01:18:11,199
Well, it's a blue ball!

1004
01:18:12,875 --> 01:18:14,637
It's a bowling ball.

1005
01:18:15,645 --> 01:18:16,906
Thank you, darling.

1006
01:18:17,013 --> 01:18:18,540
Do you like it?

1007
01:18:18,541 --> 01:18:20,140
Yes, very much. Very much.

1008
01:18:20,850 --> 01:18:21,747
Ralphie.

1009
01:18:21,951 --> 01:18:23,975
We're waiting.

1010
01:18:24,153 --> 01:18:25,710
Oh, come on, Mom.

1011
01:18:26,155 --> 01:18:27,815
Right now!

1012
01:18:37,899 --> 01:18:41,527
Lmmediately my feet began to sweat as those two fluffy little bunnies...

1013
01:18:41,603 --> 01:18:44,969
with the blue button eyes stared sappily up at me.

1014
01:18:45,708 --> 01:18:48,403
Come down here so I can see you better.

1015
01:18:49,245 --> 01:18:51,041
I just hoped Flick would never spot them...

1016
01:18:51,180 --> 01:18:54,478
as the word of this humiliation could easily make life...

1017
01:18:54,550 --> 01:18:57,382
at Warren G. Harding School a veritable hell.

1018
01:18:59,822 --> 01:19:00,810
Isn't that cute?

1019
01:19:01,490 --> 01:19:05,118
That is the most precious thing I've ever seen in my life.

1020
01:19:05,928 --> 01:19:06,825
Shut up, Randy.

1021
01:19:07,829 --> 01:19:09,921
He looks like a deranged Easter bunny.

1022
01:19:12,133 --> 01:19:13,027
He does not!

1023
01:19:13,028 --> 01:19:13,827
He does, too.

1024
01:19:13,902 --> 01:19:15,596
He looks like a pink nightmare.

1025
01:19:16,271 --> 01:19:18,261
Are you happy wearing that?

1026
01:19:18,606 --> 01:19:19,594
Do you want to take it off?

1027
01:19:19,808 --> 01:19:21,035
You tell the kid to take it off.

1028
01:19:21,109 --> 01:19:24,077
You'll only wear it when Aunt Clara visits. Go on and take it off.

1029
01:19:24,145 --> 01:19:25,805
Take it off!

1030
01:19:29,418 --> 01:19:31,317
My God, will you look at that mess?

1031
01:19:31,721 --> 01:19:33,354
Who's going to clean the papers up?

1032
01:19:33,355 --> 01:19:34,154
Not me.

1033
01:19:35,558 --> 01:19:36,789
Randy did it last year.

1034
01:19:36,790 --> 01:19:37,889
Well, he can do it again.

1035
01:19:40,462 --> 01:19:43,362
You know, this wine is not bad. It's not good either, but...

1036
01:19:43,431 --> 01:19:44,690
You want a sip?

1037
01:19:44,691 --> 01:19:45,990
No, you don't.

1038
01:19:47,469 --> 01:19:48,560
Did you have a nice Christmas?

1039
01:19:49,304 --> 01:19:50,270
Yeah, pretty nice.

1040
01:19:50,371 --> 01:19:51,837
Did you get everything you wanted?

1041
01:19:52,807 --> 01:19:54,468
Well, almost.

1042
01:19:54,469 --> 01:19:55,468
Almost?

1043
01:19:55,577 --> 01:19:57,203
Well, that's life.

1044
01:19:57,879 --> 01:19:59,573
Well, there's always next Christmas.

1045
01:20:02,817 --> 01:20:04,181
That's funny.

1046
01:20:05,086 --> 01:20:06,882
What's that over there behind the desk?

1047
01:20:07,923 --> 01:20:08,854
Where?

1048
01:20:08,924 --> 01:20:10,754
Behind the desk, against the wall over there.

1049
01:20:13,595 --> 01:20:14,925
Why don't you go check it out?

1050
01:20:31,613 --> 01:20:32,909
What did we put over there, honey?

1051
01:20:34,382 --> 01:20:36,474
Santa Claus probably put it.

1052
01:21:13,353 --> 01:21:17,186
Oh, it was beautiful. I could hardly wait to try it out.

1053
01:21:17,958 --> 01:21:19,618
Do you know how to load it?

1054
01:21:23,063 --> 01:21:24,324
That's right.

1055
01:21:32,006 --> 01:21:32,903
Be careful.

1056
01:21:33,374 --> 01:21:34,806
Don't. They run all over.

1057
01:21:41,649 --> 01:21:42,910
Close her up. Close it up.

1058
01:21:43,985 --> 01:21:46,680
Can I try it out, Ma? Can I?

1059
01:21:46,787 --> 01:21:47,553
Sure.

1060
01:21:47,554 --> 01:21:48,253
Okay.

1061
01:21:48,722 --> 01:21:49,847
But outside.

1062
01:21:49,957 --> 01:21:51,821
I still say those things are dangerous.

1063
01:21:53,327 --> 01:21:55,920
Put on your galoshes and your coat. It's cold out.

1064
01:21:59,366 --> 01:22:02,300
I had one when I was eight years old.

1065
01:22:02,903 --> 01:22:05,427
What if he hurts himself? Ralphie, your coat!

1066
01:22:06,740 --> 01:22:08,641
Don't shoot any animals or birds!

1067
01:22:08,642 --> 01:22:10,641
Except the Bumpuses' dogs!

1068
01:22:12,246 --> 01:22:14,236
Be careful, Ralphie!

1069
01:22:14,916 --> 01:22:18,009
Now it is well known throughout the Midwest that the old man...

1070
01:22:18,085 --> 01:22:19,949
is a turkey junkie.

1071
01:22:20,821 --> 01:22:25,120
A bona fide garley turkicanus freak. A few days before Christmas...

1072
01:22:25,259 --> 01:22:29,354
his eyes would begin to gleam with a wild and ravenous light.

1073
01:22:33,333 --> 01:22:37,632
Okay, Black Bart, now you get yours.

1074
01:22:51,617 --> 01:22:53,550
Oh, my God! I shot my eye out!

1075
01:22:53,719 --> 01:22:55,276
You'll shoot your eye out, kid.

1076
01:22:55,755 --> 01:23:00,020
You'll shoot your eye out, you'll shoot your eye out!

1077
01:23:00,961 --> 01:23:04,157
Ralphie, you be careful out there. Don't shoot your eye out!

1078
01:23:04,231 --> 01:23:06,289
She hadn't seen! She didn't know!

1079
01:23:06,934 --> 01:23:09,527
My eye's all right. The BB must've hit my glasses.

1080
01:23:10,938 --> 01:23:12,632
My glasses! Oh, no!

1081
01:23:12,706 --> 01:23:14,366
Where are my glasses?

1082
01:23:16,009 --> 01:23:18,772
Few things brought such swift and terrible retribution...

1083
01:23:18,879 --> 01:23:21,847
on a kid as a pair of busted glasses!

1084
01:23:26,185 --> 01:23:27,446
Stop!

1085
01:23:39,666 --> 01:23:41,132
Oh, no!

1086
01:23:43,603 --> 01:23:45,866
Oh, no! Pulverized.

1087
01:23:57,750 --> 01:24:01,913
For a moment I thought, I'll fake it. They'll never know the lens is gone!

1088
01:24:04,590 --> 01:24:07,422
Randomly, my mind evolved a spectacular plot.

1089
01:24:07,626 --> 01:24:09,786
Let's see, an icicle!

1090
01:24:10,129 --> 01:24:12,494
Falls off the garage and hits me in the eye!

1091
01:24:12,832 --> 01:24:17,029
It would work. It had to work. Quickly, I whipped up some tears.

1092
01:24:23,309 --> 01:24:26,072
What's the matter, honey? What happened?

1093
01:24:26,145 --> 01:24:27,372
What happened? Let me see that.

1094
01:24:27,446 --> 01:24:31,211
There was this icicle and it fell off the garage and it hit me.

1095
01:24:35,588 --> 01:24:36,418
What is it?

1096
01:24:36,419 --> 01:24:38,818
No, it's okay. Just read your funnies.

1097
01:24:42,995 --> 01:24:44,484
Wake up, Randy.

1098
01:24:49,268 --> 01:24:50,598
Oh, God.

1099
01:24:50,770 --> 01:24:53,829
It hit my cheek and it broke my glasses.

1100
01:24:54,340 --> 01:24:58,036
And I tried to get out of the way, but I...

1101
01:24:59,978 --> 01:25:03,879
There, see, it's just a little bump.

1102
01:25:04,250 --> 01:25:05,910
You're lucky it didn't cut your eye.

1103
01:25:05,985 --> 01:25:08,111
Those icicles have been known to kill people.

1104
01:25:14,360 --> 01:25:16,060
What's going on up there?

1105
01:25:16,061 --> 01:25:17,760
Nothing. We'll be right down.

1106
01:25:18,064 --> 01:25:20,725
You stay away from that turkey! It's got an hour to cook.

1107
01:25:20,833 --> 01:25:21,992
You'll get worms!

1108
01:25:27,172 --> 01:25:28,661
But what about my glasses?

1109
01:25:29,240 --> 01:25:31,571
You can wear the old ones with the crack in them...

1110
01:25:31,643 --> 01:25:33,473
until we get you some new ones.

1111
01:25:36,314 --> 01:25:38,213
I had pulled it off!

1112
01:25:39,617 --> 01:25:41,481
But I left my gun outside.

1113
01:25:42,787 --> 01:25:45,653
When you get dressed you can go out and get your gun.

1114
01:25:45,857 --> 01:25:47,221
Hold that on there.

1115
01:25:47,726 --> 01:25:49,317
Life is like that.

1116
01:25:49,795 --> 01:25:54,731
Sometimes at the height of our reveries, when our joy is at its zenith...

1117
01:25:54,834 --> 01:25:57,734
when all is most right with the world...

1118
01:25:57,870 --> 01:26:01,202
the most unthinkable disasters descend upon us.

1119
01:26:16,654 --> 01:26:18,211
Oh, turkey!

1120
01:26:33,071 --> 01:26:36,267
Sons a bitches! Bumpuses!

1121
01:26:51,489 --> 01:26:55,083
The heavenly aroma still hung heavy in the house. But it was gone.

1122
01:26:55,226 --> 01:26:58,251
All gone. No turkey. No turkey sandwiches.

1123
01:26:58,329 --> 01:27:02,355
No turkey salad. No turkey gravy, turkey hash, turkey a la king...

1124
01:27:02,466 --> 01:27:03,762
or gallons of turkey soup.

1125
01:27:03,834 --> 01:27:04,561
Gone.

1126
01:27:04,635 --> 01:27:05,896
All gone.

1127
01:27:10,541 --> 01:27:11,529
All right.

1128
01:27:12,010 --> 01:27:12,907
Everybody upstairs.

1129
01:27:13,144 --> 01:27:14,440
Get dressed.

1130
01:27:16,614 --> 01:27:18,103
We are going out to eat.

1131
01:27:42,406 --> 01:27:46,865
No! Not, "ra ra ra ra ra." "La la la la la."

1132
01:27:47,277 --> 01:27:48,072
Sing like this:

1133
01:27:56,521 --> 01:27:58,010
Try again.

1134
01:28:08,031 --> 01:28:09,224
Stop!

1135
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:11,762
Sing something else.

1136
01:28:25,349 --> 01:28:26,406
No!

1137
01:28:26,483 --> 01:28:27,574
Stop!

1138
01:28:28,452 --> 01:28:30,715
Kitchen. Bring food. For customers.

1139
01:28:39,863 --> 01:28:41,193
Oh, I'm sorry.

1140
01:28:44,034 --> 01:28:45,694
It's a beautiful duck.

1141
01:28:46,103 --> 01:28:47,763
It really is.

1142
01:28:48,572 --> 01:28:50,198
But you see...

1143
01:28:52,709 --> 01:28:53,504
What?

1144
01:28:53,577 --> 01:28:55,544
It's smiling at me.

1145
01:29:01,118 --> 01:29:02,209
Okay?

1146
01:29:03,620 --> 01:29:05,052
Beautiful!

1147
01:29:08,591 --> 01:29:10,615
That Christmas would live in our memories...

1148
01:29:10,726 --> 01:29:14,161
as the Christmas when we were introduced to Chinese turkey.

1149
01:29:15,598 --> 01:29:17,588
All was right with the world.

1150
01:29:38,555 --> 01:29:40,852
Oh, honey, come over here. Look at this.

1151
01:29:41,691 --> 01:29:43,658
Is that beautiful!

1152
01:30:29,605 --> 01:30:33,870
Next to me in the blackness lay my oiled blue-steel beauty.

1153
01:30:34,643 --> 01:30:36,974
The greatest Christmas gift I had ever received...

1154
01:30:37,079 --> 01:30:38,511
or would ever receive.

1155
01:30:39,682 --> 01:30:43,344
Gradually, I drifted off to sleep, pranging ducks on the wing...

1156
01:30:43,420 --> 01:30:45,944
and getting off spectacular hip shots.

